originalText.text:
First come first served? I don't think so.

I got there before 3:50pm and left without being seen at 7:10pm today... you do the math: no secretary keeping track of who's arriving, but there was a list where you're supposed to write down your name to be called in.

When I arrived, I was THE ONLY person in the waiting area (he was already working with someone). Then, a man comes 30 minutes after me and gets called inside first by first name (because he sat in a place where he could be seen from inside the preparer's office) and they could just say hi as if they ran into each other at a bodega.
I asked the woman that was gossiping and sitting next to the door area why am I not first even though I was waiting long before the aforementioned man arrived... and she lies saying that this guy was just there to sign (he stayed inside for an hour --obviously doing more than just a signature).

MORE people start to come in and signing their names, when the man that went ahead of me gets out, then another guy that came after him gets called in. Nobody is looking at the so called list they have to keep track of who's there first. So now there's two people that got there later than I did being taken care of.

I stayed sitting there like a fool, i tried to ask what is going on, but the woman is too busy to interrupt her telenovela and do her job.
I stayed there for >3 hours, and someone else is brought inside because the woman that was before me said that "he was with her".... he was NOT with her, I overheard their conversation about how he needs to fill his taxes and she was going to wait for him.

3 hours waiting. The woman sitting watching her telenovela just says "it's like that always a long wait, people leave at 10pm" (WTH?!). The thing is... I wouldn't mind the wait if there was actually people waiting before me. But there was NO ONE when I arrived, yet 3 people managed to get inside before me. Maybe if you're compadre with the guy you can get in on a fair and timely manner, otherwise I'd still be sitting there.

Avoid at all costs.

originalText.text: He is really good at his job , but if you are the type of person that doesn't like to wait then this is not the place for you, max wait time 7 hrs,  is a first come first serve, they give you an appointment but in reality is just to let them know that you will come in on that day .I suggest you arrive as early as possible and bring a bottle of water chips or even a sandwich because the wait is ridiculously long ..
